hen coupling is allowed to vary: for 3x2pt we find, at $0.5 <\nz < 1$, $\\beta=0.0180_{-0.011}^{+0.007}$, comparable to what CMB and background\ndatasets would give for a constant coupling. This makes upcoming galaxy surveys\npotentially powerful probes to test CDE models at low redshifts. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Nov 2022 13:24:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Apr 2023 16:27:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-13"}
